Anthony Joshua's long-awaited rematch against Oleksandr Usyk will be delayed until July after Eddie Hearn and Alexander Krassyuk held fresh talks over a new fight date, according to reports. The Brit lost his world heavyweight titles to Usyk when the pair traded blows for the first time back in September and will be desperate to avenge his latest defeat with a much-improved showing at the next time of asking. MORE TO FOLLOW We'll be bringing you the very latest updates, pictures and video on this breaking news story. Stay up to date with all the big headlines, pictures, analysis, opinion and video on the stories that matter to you. Follow us on Twitter @DExpress_Sport - the official Daily Express & Express.co.uk Twitter account - providing real news in real time. We're also on Facebook offering your must-see news, features, videos and pictures throughout the day to like, comment and share from the Daily Express, Sunday Express and Express.co.uk.